<span id="freeTextContainer2328650313113807394">A mesmerizing read that made me want to seek out the women of Tennessee&apos;s fog and revisit all of his plays. Tennessee&apos;s deep love of women, the “saints” on his rosary of the theater, in his life - some as flawed and needy as he - are such a joy to read about in his words and in theirs as author Grissom goes about his assignment of seeking them out, to ask if Tennessee Williams mattered. He did. </span>
  <span id="freeText2328650313113807394" style="display:none">A mesmerizing read that made me want to seek out the women of Tennessee's fog and revisit all of his plays. Tennessee's deep love of women, the “saints” on his rosary of the theater, in his life - some as flawed and needy as he - are such a joy to read about in his words and in theirs as author Grissom goes about his assignment of seeking them out, to ask if Tennessee Williams mattered. He did. </span>
