        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2660899095" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7378253096195122680">Williams met with a twenty-year-old Grissom as the result or a fan letter. He gave the young man a formidable assignment to contact a list of actresses Williams had been associated with to determine if William&apos;s contact with them had made a difference in their lives. Twenty years later he was able to complete the assignment and this book is the result. An unconventional biography that reveals and speculates on Williams&apos;s life through the lens of women and some men. Gossipy in parts. Candid. Brin</span>
  <span id="freeText7378253096195122680" style="display:none">Williams met with a twenty-year-old Grissom as the result or a fan letter. He gave the young man a formidable assignment to contact a list of actresses Williams had been associated with to determine if William's contact with them had made a difference in their lives. Twenty years later he was able to complete the assignment and this book is the result. An unconventional biography that reveals and speculates on Williams's life through the lens of women and some men. Gossipy in parts. Candid. Bring your own lens to this fascinating, but perhaps rather long voyage through Tennessee Williams Land.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7378253096195122680" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
