        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781101972779" href="/book/show/28503872-follies-of-god">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1814755428" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3735294370415837757">Riveting and intense. A unique biography / memoir hybrid that encompasses the life and career of Tennessee Williams, the space of 20th century film and theater history that he occupied, and the author&apos;s own personal experience with Williams. It&apos;s a fascinating inside look at the lives of some really notable show biz figures that probes much deeper than most other books in this realm. Basically, it&apos;s a must-read for those (like myself) who love stories like these.</span>
  <span id="freeText3735294370415837757" style="display:none">Riveting and intense. A unique biography / memoir hybrid that encompasses the life and career of Tennessee Williams, the space of 20th century film and theater history that he occupied, and the author's own personal experience with Williams. It's a fascinating inside look at the lives of some really notable show biz figures that probes much deeper than most other books in this realm. Basically, it's a must-read for those (like myself) who love stories like these.</span>
